JOHANNESBURG - President Jacob Zuma has bid farewell to the outgoing leadership of the ANC, as the party prepares for its elective conference. Zuma gave his final gala dinner speech as ANC leader. In his keynote address, the president praised the ANC. The President was accompanied by his wife Thobeka Zuma and sat next to Cosatu president Sdumo Dlamini. The event was well attended by the major players in the business world with presidential hopeful Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma, embracing businessman Patrice Motsepe and his wife Precious Moloi-Motsepe. Zuma jokingly mentioned how some of the current top six members will be coming back to leadership. “But I’d also want to thank my colleagues, the Top 6 of the ANC, especially, when I’m not there, the one who becomes a number..I did not know, I heard that when I’m not there I’m called a number, when I’m not there he becomes a U number, u Deputy President, ubaba u Cyril Ramaphosa. He is outgoing as well but he will come back, I’m told," said President Jacob Zuma. eNCA